So I'm going to hand it over to you.

00:02:13.760 --> 00:02:17.580
And maybe you can kick us off with some of the approaches

00:02:17.580 --> 00:02:21.300
that you have seen that have worked and maybe what's changing

00:02:21.300 --> 00:02:22.000
a little bit.

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:26.000
Thanks.

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:27.800
Yeah, as mentioned, I'm Andre Renensland.

00:02:27.800 --> 00:02:30.990
I run the news feed and trending news feeds on Blue Sky

00:02:30.990 --> 00:02:31.160
.

00:02:31.160 --> 00:02:34.280
And what has worked?

00:02:34.280 --> 00:02:37.160
Well, so some of the things I find that really connect

00:02:37.160 --> 00:02:40.180
with publishers is the identity system is like a really big part

00:02:40.290 --> 00:02:42.990
of it, both in terms of being able to set your

00:02:42.990 --> 00:02:48.680
username to your domain name for your newspaper, as well as

00:02:48.680 --> 00:02:51.640
the new verification system, I think is really cool as well

00:02:51.640 --> 00:02:54.920
, for news orgs to be able to verify their own

00:02:54.920 --> 00:03:00.070
journalists instead of having to wait for some large tech company apparatus

00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:00.920
to do that for them.

00:03:00.920 --> 00:03:02.760
I think it's like a really powerful feature.

00:03:02.760 --> 00:03:06.310
I'd also really love to see journalism societies kind of start

00:03:06.310 --> 00:03:09.750
using more of the affordances of the platform in that way

00:03:09.760 --> 00:03:10.120
.

00:03:10.120 --> 00:03:13.470
Like for instance, like having, you know, journalism,

00:03:13.480 --> 00:03:17.120
journalist unions might be like a really powerful place for doing the

00:03:17.120 --> 00:03:17.960
verification layer.

00:03:17.960 --> 00:03:20.680
I'm not sure if I answered the question in terms of

00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:21.080
what's worked.

00:03:21.080 --> 00:03:27.320
I think in general, the reach that Blue Sky gives news

00:03:27.420 --> 00:03:29.230
orgs is really, really good.

00:03:29.230 --> 00:03:32.100
And the kind of traffic that news orgs are getting from

00:03:32.330 --> 00:03:33.780
Blue Sky is really impressive.

00:03:33.780 --> 00:03:35.320
Anecdotally, I've talked to a few

00:03:35.320 --> 00:03:38.660
orgs who have said that Blue Sky traffic has kind of

00:03:38.660 --> 00:03:42.140
outpaced a lot of other social networks, even ones that

00:03:42.140 --> 00:03:44.190
are like much, much bigger than Blue Sky.

00:03:44.190 --> 00:03:47.970
And I think that is reflective of just how engaged with news

00:03:47.970 --> 00:03:51.160
the Blue Sky community is and the atmosphere in general.

00:03:51.160 --> 00:03:56.560
And it's interesting how there's kind of been this movement

00:03:56.560 --> 00:04:00.660
of people who are really seriously interested in journalism to the platform

00:04:00.660 --> 00:04:00.830
.

00:04:00.830 --> 00:04:03.140
And I think kind of as builders, it's important to

00:04:03.250 --> 00:04:06.120
think, how do we keep the momentum going and how do

00:04:06.120 --> 00:04:10.790
we encourage more people to start making use of those affordances

00:04:10.950 --> 00:04:11.240
?

00:04:11.340 --> 00:04:12.800
Because I think kind of at this point, like, you

00:04:12.800 --> 00:04:14.410
're right, like, you know, kind of trying to

00:04:14.410 --> 00:04:17.160
bully people off of Twitter so that they just use Blue Sky

00:04:17.320 --> 00:04:21.720
is probably a bit of a diminishing return strategy at this

00:04:21.720 --> 00:04:21.960
point.

00:04:21.960 --> 00:04:26.280
I think how we win is we start showing how the afford

00:04:26.280 --> 00:04:30.920
ances of the platform of the atmosphere lend themselves to really good

00:04:30.920 --> 00:04:33.320
journalism and good engagement with audience.

00:04:33.320 --> 00:04:37.240
Thank you, Andra.

