Um, so they can't be, um, on the

00:06:42.120 --> 00:06:43.070
feed all day.

00:06:43.070 --> 00:06:46.490
Um, some certainly are anyway, uh, there's definitely

00:06:46.500 --> 00:06:49.880
an addictive property of, of microblogging.

00:06:49.880 --> 00:06:52.220
Um, but, uh, I find a lot of journalists

00:06:52.220 --> 00:06:53.660
are like, well, I, you know, I've

00:06:53.660 --> 00:06:56.420
got to write and go to my meetings and do my thing

00:06:56.420 --> 00:06:58.690
, but I can come back to SIL throughout the day

00:06:58.760 --> 00:07:01.480
and see what the conversation has been at a glance, uh

00:07:01.480 --> 00:07:04.360
, rather than having to scroll the three hours of my timeline

00:07:04.360 --> 00:07:05.240
that I missed.

